4 §6301. Student health Communicable or infectious disease
5 The following provisions apply to a student health showing symptoms of a
6 communicable or infectious disease.
7 1. Duty of teacher school personnel. A teacher member of school personnel who has
8 reason to believe that a student is a public health threat as a result of having a communicable
9 disease of the skin, mouth or eyes showing symptoms of a communicable or infectious
10 disease reportable under Title 22, chapter 250, subchapter 3 or that pose a public health
11 threat shall inform the superintendent or the superintendent's designee.
12 2. Duty of superintendent. A superintendent or a superintendent's designee informed
13 by a teacher a member of school personnel under subsection 1 may:
14 A. Inform Advise the student's parent: to furnish the student with the required home
15 or medical treatment for the relief of the student's symptoms or disease reported under
16 subsection 1;
17 (1) To cleanse the clothing and body of the student; and
18 (2) To furnish the student with the required home or medical treatment for the
19 relief of the student's trouble so defined in subsection 1;
20 B. Exclude the student from the public schools until the student is no longer a public
21 health threat;
22 C. Exclude the student from public school as soon as safe and proper transportation
23 home is available; and
24 D. Consult with the school nurse.
25 3. Duty of parent. A parent informed by a superintendent or the superintendent's
26 designee under subsection 2 shall promptly do what is reasonably necessary to ensure that
27 the student is not a public health threat.
28 4. Penalty. Any parent who fails to comply with subsection 3 shall be fined not more
29 than $5 for the first offense or $10 for subsequent offenses.
30 5-A. Notification. The A superintendent or the superintendent's designee informed
31 by a member of school personnel under subsection 1 shall cause notice of the
32 communicable or infectious disease to be given to the Department of Health and Human
33 Services, in accordance with the requirements of Title 22, chapters 250 and 251, and rules
34 issued under those chapters.
35 6. Authority and duties of the Department of Health and Human Services. The
36 Department of Health and Human Services has the authority and duties prescribed in Title
37 22, chapters 250 and 251 with respect to the control of notifiable diseases and conditions
38 and communicable or infectious diseases.
