28 SUMMARY
2299 This bill clarifies the duties of school personnel, superintendents and parents with
3300 regard to reporting symptoms of communicable or infectious diseases. The bill also
3311 clarifies that the duty for school nurses to supervise and coordinate health-related activities
3322 must be carried out in accordance with the most recent school nursing practices and follow
3333 all applicable rules adopted by the State Board of Nursing. The bill also requires the
3344 guidelines on the provision of school health services and health-related activities to be
3355 based on state and national standards and updated at least every 3 years. The bill also
3366 updates the term "epinephrine autoinjector" to "epinephrine automated device."
